title: Vanguard FTSE Pacific Breaks Above 200-Day Moving Average - Bullish for VPL - Nasdaq.com
text: In trading on Thursday, shares of the Vanguard FTSE Pacific ETF (Symbol: VPL) crossed above their 200 day moving average of $64.71, changing hands as high as $64.86 per share. Vanguard FTSE Pacific shares are currently trading up about 1% on the day. The chart below shows the one year performance of VPL shares, versus its 200 day moving average:     Looking at the chart above, VPL's low point in its 52 week range is $58.6182 per share, with $71.68 as the 52 week high point - that compares with a last trade of $64.82.
